  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Democracy, Justice and Peace</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objectives of the programme were to deepen democracy; increase respect for human rights; ensure legal rights of the poor, and; peace and reconciliation. The programme emphasised three components which was mutually reinforcing: 1) Democracy and human rights; 2) Justice and legal rights of the poor, and; 3) To promote peace and reconciliation. Component one aimed at improving the opportunities for the Ugandan&#xBF;s to participate and affect the democratisation process i.a. through support for civil society. Moreover, through support of the Ugandan Human Rights Commission, a contribution to adherence to human rights was made. Through the second component, the objectives were to strengthen the courts and consolidate the law-sector. In addition, the establishment of a law and justice fund, which developed new models for legal procedures, in preparation to secure that justice and law reached the most impoverished segments. Component three strengthened the country&#xBF;s capacity of peace and reconciliation.</narrative>
  </description>
